data.title: Alexander III and Maria Marriage Medalette, Jeton, Russia
data.meta_description: Commemorating the marriage of Alexander III and Maria Feodorovna this medalette was minted in Russia in 1866. Alexander III ruled Russia from 1881-1894 and was affectionately known as The Peacemaker as Russia refused to engage in any wars during his reign.Obverse inscription: Ð’.
